Traffic officials have called on motorists to seek alternative routes following the closure of the N3 Highway in Mooi River KwaZulu-Natal as a result of violent protests. Eighteen trucks were torched and allegedly looted late last night following a violent service delivery protest. Both north and southbound carriageways remain closed as mop-up operations are underway. It is currently not clear why the trucks were targeted by the protestors. According to reports, protestors allegedly opened fire on the police using live ammunition’ however, these reports have not yet been confirmed by the police. Another similar protest erupted during the Easter weekend prompting Police Minister Bheki Cele to visit the area. Several police units remain stationed in the area. -Afroworld View 